      • invariant

        public static FunctionReturnTypeResolver invariant​(BasicType<?> invariantType)
        A resolver that defines an invariant result type. E.g. `substring` always returns a String. Note however that to account for attribute converters and such, this resolver allows the context-impled expression type to be the return type so long as the Java types are compatible.
